caption: Try the picnic board!
Salad was frozen or close too. Prosciutto pizza was basically all crust. Not their best night
Would absolutely recommend eating here. Fantastic ambience, yummy dishes, good customer service. They never disappoint.
The Buffalo Brussels Sprouts are sublime.  Any of the pizzas are great
Take out charcuterie and burrata are great to go.
Great food and atmosphere. Had a really fun time. Hidden gem

Really cool vibes in this place. Affordable wine, good selection of drinks. Pizza’s also good. Like not earth-shatteringly good, but very, very decent. We tried the Alsacian, and the prosciutto pairs nicely with caramelized onions & gruyere cheese. My only concern - they discontinued their Tuesday night special (drinks and pizza for $18), but forgot to reprint the menus.   The special is displayed prominently on the menu page, so hearing that it won’t be honored can get someone in a bad mood.
We discovered Altari Brothers in April and haven't gone anywhere else for pizza since!  Great pizza and appetizers plus very helpful staff that will accommodate curbside/contactless carryout.

Have been gettin Alatri brothers pretty regularly during quarantine.   The food is amazing.  I think I’ve tried all the pizzas now and love them all.  Don’t miss the wings or Caesar salad either.  Can’t wait to return to dining at the restaurant.

Alatari bros is the best pizza I’ve ever had. I went here for my birthday, that’s how much I love it. The pizzas are so fresh and yummy, the pasta is great too, and the deserts are super great too. My favorite pizza is the classic, margarita.

I love this spot! They prepare good meals, they have a nice menu, The chief cook in that place is a real authority in the kitchen, I enjoy a lot eating all their food. The food is consistently of high class, the service towards the guests  is agreeable. I frequently visit this place and I not even once was discontended. I recommend it to all my friends.
Great wines by the glass
The pizza and appetizers on the menu are excellent. Great outdoor vibe and great place for dinner in nicer weather.

Their pizza doesn't have sauce. It's super weird. The alsacian is not an alsacian pizza. Alsacien pizza is made with creme fresh, this has nothing on it. The brussels sprout appetizer is super good though
An amazing pizza place. I would definitely recommend. One of the best pizzas I have ever had.
Great food, great beer and outstanding service
Nice local pizza joint (easy to overlook!) next to the Gringos and Mariachis. Really good fire baked pizza, good apps and nice beer selection. And prices are affordable. Will be back.
Great pizza and great service
You cannot go wrong with anything on the menu. Pizza is made in wood-fired oven. Be careful with appetizers - the main meal is enough food.

Is this a great fire cooked pizza shop in Bethesda that you would probably miss if you weren't looking for it. The ingredients of the pizza are absolutely excellent I need very well. The staff work hard and are very friendly. The outdoor seating area has many chairs and some lovely shade. Overall a great experience.
Best crust in Bethesda
I expected better everything seemed to be kind of dried and worn-out I really did it hope for a better experience
Best owner and bartender's in bethesda

Come for the atmosphere and pizza.  Been here a few times now and have really enjoyed the atmosphere. Seems to always have a busy vibe, music is noticeable but not overpowering. Wait staff is friendly and def you can tell there is solid teamwork within their ranks.  Food is great, but I haven’t tried the whole menu. Buratta is fabulous! Buffalo Brussels sprouts make a tasty snack. The heaping fresh greens with sundry cheeses fruits and veggies make for generously portioned salads. Pizza is cooked in a stone wood fired oven. Dough is amazing, some of the best. Calzone was ok, large portion, simple ingredients.  Price is very reasonable. For two: full sangria carafe, two apps, a pizza and pasta was ~50$, plus tip.  Great value at Altri Bros on this foodie street in Bethesda
Great pizza!  Good service!  Get the PBS deal!  It’s worth it!
Excellent service and friendly staff. Great food every single time. Absolute five star.
The pizzas are really good and service is good without being pushy. Apps are large enough to share. Very good sortiment of beer and wine.
Try the whipped feta!
Great pizza
Great pizzas and super friendly and attentive service. Decent selection of craft beers and wine.
Get the burrata! Super delicious and creamy. Amazing and
Great pizza
Amazing pizza, some of the best I've had.
Friendly service and good for families. But the food isn't that great. It's definitely not bad. It's just OK.
Cam here for restaurant week. Amazing appetizers, white feta pizza and buffalo brussel sprouts especially!
Awesome food 👏🏽

I don't go to Alatri Bros nearly as much as I should. I always get one of their Boards (usually the Picnic Platter) and a Pizza. Both of those shared between two is plenty. I've never had a bad time here.
Fantastic place!! #Bethesdabodyworks for your hot off the press Masaage!!

My calazone was badly cooked and the dough was raw in some places.  That was unfortunate since high quality ingredients were used.  There were reals balls of mozerella.  (Not melted because miscooked).  Pepperoni was tasty.  Service was friendly.  It is likely I would have given this 5 stars if properly cooked.
Pretty underwhelmed by the food. Got the special pizza and it wasn’t as described.
Good pizza, cauliflower appetizer is tasty!
Good food, great service.
Good place, good pizza, fun atmosphere in a good spot. Best neopolitan pizza in Bethesda downtown. I also like that you can order food from their sister/neighbor restaurant Gringos and Mariachis.
This place is awesome. The food is great, Donnie is a fantastic bartender and the atmosphere is fantastic.

I've been there 2 weeks ago with my friends. They ordered special pizzas and we're very good. I ordered a margherita pizza and it was so dry. Obviously I ate, was good. Also I check the menu in Google and it wasn't that same that they have there. I suppose that I need give them a second chance.
This place tries hard. And looks the part. But the pizza’s just not that good. It’s serviceable, but that’s it. So in a pinch, it’ll work. But if you’re looking for outstanding pizza, look elsewhere.
Nice pizza! BUT: Waiter rushing bill and took away my half full beer while I was visiting the restroom.

Service was decent and the food was good. Nice selection of beers to choose from. The pizza crust and toppings were all good quality, and it was cooked properly (thank you!). We especially liked the veggie board, what a delicious way to get your daily intake. They share a covered patio with the taco place nextdoor; we enjoyed being able to sit outside while also getting out of the sun.
Food was great. Came out quick. Love this place.

Great pizza place! The pizza crust is amazing, we ordered the tomato and mozzarella pie and added pepperoni and mushrooms! Nice fresh ingredients! There are also other options on the menu, we ordered a side of hand cut fries and they were nice and thick! Delicious. We will definitely be back! I loved the environment and how there is indoor and outdoor seating.
Nice and cozy.  Pizza is delicious.
Great food and service!
Great bartenders, great pizza. I also highly recommend the cauliflower fritti - so good. The Tuesday deal is also a go-getter, $18 for a pizza, beer, and shot, show me a better deal in Bethesda.
Good food & service
Nice restaurant for a casual dinner, a bit congested seating though!
Donny is a very attentive and friendly bartender.
Good pizza all around.
Great time was had by all. The food was delish. Can't wait to come back again.
Great wood burning pizza. The whipped feta and chicken wing appetizers are a must-try.
Great service, solid menu and excellent quality in food. Cozy atmosphere with good outdoor seating too.
Amazing food and beer!!!

This place was fantastic and although similar to its predecessor (Mia's Pizza) the other options besides pizza are better than before. Every part of the pizza I had was amazing and perfectly cooked. I tried to the Crazy Calabrese which was perfectly made and all the toppings were delicious. The appetizers we tried were also very good, the eat your veggies board and hot wings were large portions and were all good in their own way. I will def be back.

We stumbled upon Alatri and decided to give it a try. Wow!! We ordered the meatballs sliders (no bun) and it was full of flavor. We each ordered a main, chicken alfredo and shrimp fra diavolo, both were good. The alfredo had mushroom and the sauce was light which made it healthy. The shrimp was just as good and not super spicy as most far diavolo sauces made elsewhere. Definitely should go and try
Best pizza
Ordered takeout, food was absolutely disgusting
Renovations look great, love the crazy calabrese pizza nice mix of spicy and sweet. Also buffalo brussel sprouts are delicious!
LOVED THIS PLACE! Best pizza crust I've ever had, nice atmosphere, friendly staff, quick service. Definitely recommend.
Highly recommended the Smores cake dessert. Anything on the menu pizza is a solid choice. Fun fact: owned by the same group that also owns Gringo's (next door) and Olazzo.
Best pizza in Bethesda hands down.
Love this place.  I wish it wasn't so fattening.

I have had great pizza many times in the past but had not gone to Mia's in a while.  Last night, we went and the pizza wasn't quite as good.  In addition, my wife had the pasta with shrimp and was sick half the night.  She was fine this morning which leads us to believe that it was most likely the pasta dish.
Love their tasty pizza and quick services!
You must try Formaggio Pizza with sausage and bacon.
Friendly staff (which is always important), good pizza and overall nice environment. The only problem is that its kind of hidden and hard to find.
Started my birthday pizza crawl bright and early with a morning Margherita pizza at Mia's. Absolutely worth every bite.
Nice neighborhood spot. Great salads and apps. Pizzas are just the right size and well cooked in wood oven. A tad noisy but friendly and efficient service. We'll be back!
Fantastic!
We moved here from Napoli, Italia in July and Mia's Pizza is far and above the most authentic and delicious in the area.  Our server Christian was great and our lunch experience was fantastic.
Great pizza place.
Great pizza awesome for family night out.

My girlfriend and I went in to grab a pizza to go. I stepped into the restroom while she waited at the bar and ordered a beer. The manager or owner lady asked for her ID. When I returned she had just come back and told her she refused to serve her because she had a license from another state. We asked why and she rudely said, "It's my prerogative. Montgomery County has strict rules."  We were embarrassed and highly upset. We informed her that it was a real ID and you can call the police to check if you don't believe us.  We decided we didn't want to give them any business and walked out immediately.  Being almost 30 yrs old and having this disrespect occur towards us was embarrassing.  We heard rave reviews about this place, hoping our first time would be great but now we refuse to go.  We told our friends what happened and they won't be going either.  You need to learn how to read a real ID or invest in an ID scanner because the DC area is a hub for people from other states.
Food and service was good. The 'Ultimate S’more' surprisingly made it to my list of favorite desserts.

I'd heard that Mia's had great pizza (cooked in a wood-burning oven). I had the alsace pizza and my husband had the formaggio. Unfortunately both were a big disappointment. The crust was not thin, it was tasteless and too chewy and oily (there was a layer of oil on the plate beneath the pizza as well, disgusting). It tasted like it had been reheated or kept waiting around. We were certainly kept waiting around, as it took half an hour for our pizzas to arrive. It was a Thursday evening around 6, and the place was not busy, so I don't know what the problem was. The staff were pleasant, that's what the 1 star is for! We won't be going back and I won't be recommending the place to anyone.
Very good pizza
we've only really tried their pizzas and been very pleased each time. their prices are reasonable and the service was quite good.

God made food is not good enough for service this bad. I waited 1h 30min before I got anything to eat, with a reservation. The restaurant is noisy, small and they overbook the place completely. Waiting outside is not an option because of the weather ,so every new comer is stuck in a tiny hallway, back to back, waiting prolonged amounts of time. Food was good but mias pizze needs to know the limits of their small space.
Pizza is always heavenly, so are the salads and bruschetta. Haven't had one thing here I didn't like. The chef always asks how everything went. Service is so-so but the food makes it not matter.

The food taste great.  The wife and I sat at the table for over 5 minutes waiting for the server and we waited for over an hour from time of order to the pizza coming to the table.  I'm betting the service is better during non peak times.
The service was slow considering it was a Monday. The bruscheta was nice w a tinge of balsamic redtn. Vegetale is one of the better veggie options :)
great pizza; nearly as good as the two amy's with out the crowds or the drive to dc.  good salads, especially the arugula, pear and blue cheese.
